Evaluation methodology: The submission has multiple paths through which adoption decisions can be reached without an honest real-LLM comparison. We expected something that converges on a single canonical evaluation path that produces honest results regardless of which way they point, rather than multiple fallbacks where some paths lean toward acceptance.
Real-LLM convergence evidence: The reproducibility example referenced in the README represents a degraded run with no live LLM interaction. The core deliverable is empirical evidence that the self-learning loop converges under real conditions, and that evidence isn't established at the level the assignment expects.
Cross-modal handoff completeness: The chat → voice transition is demonstrated and the live audio is real. The  voice → chat resumption with state continuity from the call back into the next chat agent isn't surfaced in the demo or in the handoff. The cross-modal round-trip is the central architectural problem of the assignment, and only one direction is demonstrated.
Architectural rigor on explicit constraints: The 2000-token-per-agent budget is enforced on response usage returned by the LLM API, not on total context including the input prompt. 
